</section>
<section class="image-text-container">
  <div class="left-header">
    <h3>How do Eye Doctors Check for Glaucoma?</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="description">
    <p>There are three major signs that a person may have glaucoma: optic nerve damage, vision loss (visual field loss) and increased eye pressure (elevated intraocular pressure). Your eye doctor has a number of tests to check for these signs.</p>
    <a href="#" class="arrow">Learn More</a>
  </div>
</section>
<section class="image-text-container">
  <div class="left-header">
    <h3>Treatment</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="description">
    <p>Glaucoma can usually be treated and controlled using medicine(s), laser surgery, glaucoma surgery or a combination of these treatments.</p>
    <a href="#" class="arrow">Learn More</a>
  </div>
</section>
